text:
(1)
East River, shoreline, north from East 94th Street, showing (background) P.S. 99, on East 99th Street between the river and First Ave. Also shown (right background) is a portion of Ward's Island.
September 23, 1935.
P. L. Sperr.

(2)
The same, from a point farther north (East 98th Street) and showing a closer view of Wards Island.
August 31, 1935.
P. L. Sperr.

(3)
A portion of the view seen in No. 1 and showing a fuller view of the Consolidated Edison Power house at the foot of East 95th to 96th Street block.
September 20, 1934.
title: East River - Shore and skyline of Manhattan from East 94th Street - Queensborough Bridge - [Consolidated Edison Company.]
